This paper discusses the issue of data security in the context of cyber-attacks on the U.S. government, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on text data and the challenge of automatically detecting the security classification of unstructured text, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as topic modeling and clustering. Therefore, the paper is also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
